Question 1: Steps when working

----------Situation 1: New to the project
Step 1: Clone project
- Git clone
Step 2: Check out from master to working on our local -- Create new branch
- Git checkout -b <branch name>
Step 3: working on local branch
Step 4: Git status and git add to update the change into git
- Git status
- Git add .
- Git status
Step 5: Git push working's branch into main repository
- Git push origin <branch name>
Step 6: Create a PR and wait for merge

----------Situation 2: Currently working with the project
Step 1: Stay at master, pull latest code into our local
- Git pull
Step 2: Check out from master to working on our local -- Create new branch
- Git checkout -b <branch name>
Step 3: Git status and git add to update the change into git
- Git status
- Git add .
- Git status
Step 4: Git push working's branch into main repository
- Git push origin <branch name>
Step 5: Create a PR and wait for merge

Question 2: Steps to rebase
Step 1: git rebase master
Step 2: git add .
Step 3: git rebase continue





